            <h6 class="mt-5 mb-4">Before Getting Started let me give you some insights of which books we will be covering in this Blog Post :-</h6>
            <div >
                <p><a href="#The_Art_of_Computer_Programming">The Art of Computer Programming</a></p>
                <p><a href="#Programming_Pearls">Programming Pearls</a></p>
                <p><a href="#Automating_the_Boring_Stuff_With_Python">Automating the Boring Stuff With Python</a></p>
                <p><a href="#Clean_Code">Clean Code: A Handbook of Agile Software Craftsmanship</a></p>
                <p><a href="#The_Self_Taught_Programmer">The Self-Taught Programmer: The Definitive Guide to Programming Professionally</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-5"> 
            Since we are in the digital era and everything is going digital , So programming has become an important part of our life. So to start a new career as a coder , you might need some resources that will let you get started. So if you want to learn programming by reading books , you might have many questions like ...
            <ul>
                <li>which book should i read ?</li>
                <li>what are the best books that the programmers are reading right now ?</li>
            </ul>

            So here are these 5 books that will teach you everything from programming fundamentals to industry recommended practices for writing code , from avoiding bugs to refactoring the code. These are the best books that you must read in 2023.

        </p>
        <!-- ========================================================================================================================== -->

      <div>
        <h4 id="The_Art_of_Computer_Programming" class="mt-5 fw-bold"> 1) The Art of Computer Programming</h4>
        <p class="mx-4 text-bg-light">– by Donald E. Knuth , published in 1968
        </p>

        <div class="book_img_container my-4">
            <img class="book_img_responsive" src="/blog-img/ArtOfComputerProgramming.png" alt="">
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4">
            <b>"</b>The Art of Computer Programming <b>"</b> also called as <b> TAOCP </b>is a comprehensive monograph that represents many programming algorithms and their analysis.
            This book also tries to cover other aspects of computer science. It's initial volumes focuses on mathematical computing and ideas like recursion and lexical scanning . This book might be difficult for a beginner to understand , So you should be little familiar with computer science before reading this.

        </p>

       <p>
        The bible of all fundamental algorithms and the work that taught many of today’s software developers most of what they know about computer programming. <br>
        – <b> Byte</b> , September 1995


       </p>

       <p>
         If you think you’re a really good programmer… read [Knuth’s] Art of Computer Programming… You should definitely send me a résumé if you can read the whole thing. <br>
         – <b> Bill Gates</b> 
       </p>
      </div>

      <!-- ======================================================================================================================================= -->

      <div>
        <h4 id="Programming_Pearls" class="mt-5 fw-bold ">2) Programming Pearls</h4>
        <p class="mx-4 text-bg-light">
            – by Jon Bentley , published in 1986
        </p>
        
        <div class="book_img_container my-4">
            <img class="book_img_responsive" src="/blog-img/programmin pearls.png" alt="">
        </div>

        <p  class="mt-4">
            <b>"</b>Programming Pearls <b>"</b> is a book that encourages the development of <b> problem solving skills</b> .This book offers many practical problems that increases the problem solving ability .So as a software enginner one must have the critical and creative thinking to solve various programming challenges . It covers many engineering techniques and is one of the most recommended book.
        </p>
        
      </div>

      <!-- =================================================================================================================================== -->

      <div>
        <h4 id="Automating_the_Boring_Stuff_With_Python" class="mt-5 fw-bold">3) Automating the Boring Stuff With Python</h4>
        <p class="mx-4 text-bg-light">
            – by AI Sweigart , published on 14, April 2015
        </p>
        
        <div class="book_img_container my-4">
            <img class="book_img_responsive" src="/blog-img/Automating the Boring Stuff With Python.png" alt="">
        </div>

        <p  class="mt-4">
            If you are a beginner then this book is for you. This is a purely a book for beginners who wants to learn coding . The book mentions easy and step by step understandable explanations of each program . It contains many practice programs that will make you an expert in coding . Once you mastered  these basic concepts , it will lead you to ....
            <ul>
                <li>Split, merge, and encryption pdfs </li>
                <li>how to Send reminder emails and text notifications</li>
                <li>Create, update, move, and rename files and folders</li>
            </ul>
            and many more automation stuff.
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- =================================================================================================================================== -->

      <div>
        <h4 id="Clean_Code" class="mt-5 fw-bold">4) Clean Code: A Handbook of Agile Software Craftsmanship</h4>
        <p class="mx-4 text-bg-light">
            – by Robert C Martin , Published 1, August 2008
        </p>
        
        <div class="book_img_container my-4">
            <img class="book_img_responsive" src="/blog-img/clean code.png" alt="">
        </div>
       
        <p class="mt-4">
            This is a great book that teaches you how to write clean code , it differentiates between a good and bad code and how can a bad code be good for someone and  even a bad code can work better . It contains many principles , patterns , OOPs concepts and improves the state of craftmanship . But the coding part is mainly done in java that build a strong foundation. 
        </p>

      <!-- =================================================================================================================================== -->

      <div>
        <h4 id="The_Self_Taught_Programmer" class="mt-5 fw-bold">5) The Self-Taught Programmer: The Definitive Guide to Programming Professionally
        </h4>
        <p class="mx-4 text-bg-light">
            – by Cory Althoff , published in 2017
        </p>

        
        <div class="book_img_container my-4">
            <img class="book_img_responsive" src="/blog-img/The Self-Taught Programmer The Definitive Guide to Programming Professionally.png" alt="">
        </div>


        <p class="mt-4">
            This book can be of great help to all the self taught programmers to enhance their programming skills . Author Cory Althoff is also a self taught programmer  who became a software engineer at eBay. As he joined eBay , he found that he still needs to learn a lot to be a professional programmer. He describes all the essential topics like object oriented programming for beginners , different algorithms and coding practices that will make you industry ready.
        </p>

        
      

